==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
[[Image:Kumquat-Crosssection.jpeg|thumb|kumquat fruits]]
# A small, orange citrus-like fruit which is native to Asia.

===Etymology===
*From Cantonese [[柑橘]].  The original Mandarin Chinese name is [[金橘]].

===Alternative spellings===
* [[cumquat]]

===Translations===
*Chinese: [[金橘]] (standard/Mandarin); [[柑橘]] (Cantonese)
*Greek: κουμ κουάτ, κουμ-κουάτ, κουμκουάτ
*Japanese: ''[[kinkan]]'' ([[キンカン]])
*Korean: ''geumgyul'' ([[금귤]])
*Thai: ''[[somchíd]]'' (ส้มจี๊ด)
*Vietnamese: ''[[cẩm quất]]'' (derived from the Cantonese) or, less commonly, ''(quả) kim quất'' (if transliterated from the characters 金橘 into Sino-Vietnamese; "quả" (果) is the Sino-Vietnamese prefix for "fruit")

